The paper discusses the Kolkata Paise Restaurant (KPR) problem, which is a resource allocation problem involving coordination and anti-coordination games. This problem is typically studied in the field of game theory, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also mentions ongoing experimental analysis of the KPR problem, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the KPR problem has applications in economic and social phenomena, which could place it under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
